        "id": 1148599
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-09-20T22:36:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Suggestion: Put both size and contents in a sub-message which only has a value if the contents are embedded. Otherwise, leave it empty. Not sure if that\u0027s a great idea, but maybe it could make things a bit clearer? In particular, I feel like the size isn\u0027t always that useful, unless the contents are also here? Not sure what the intention of the size field is.",
      "revId": "c8cb76247ccf8e942be52cf2b7da9a0015438e9a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e39189c1_23aa1d0d",
        "filename": "results/proto/v1/common.proto",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 175,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-09-20T23:20:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "added an intention.\n\nif the content is embedded, the size is not that useful because we can simply take the length of the content. But if it is stored elsewhere, it is harder to tell the size, hence the field is here.\n\nif size is populated conditionally, the consuming code will be more complicated because it must have an if statement \"if content is embedded, takes its length, otherwise use this size\". It is simpler not to have the if statement",
      "parentUuid": "6d2fabd3_0a106b78",
      "revId": "c8cb76247ccf8e942be52cf2b7da9a0015438e9a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
